The paper proposes a novel embedding model for knowledge base completion, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The model uses hyperbolic space to better reflect the topological properties of knowledge bases, which is a topic of interest in the field of geometric deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with knowledge bases, which are a type of database, and thus could be categorized under databases (cs.DB). The model's performance is evaluated on link prediction datasets, which is a common task in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
